Reasoning: The paper is focused on evaluating a development framework for engineering IoT applications, which falls under the category of IoT (Internet of Things). Therefore, cs.IOT is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the effort required for application development, reusability of software artifacts, memory metrics, and comparison with state of the art in IoT application development, which are all related to software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the characteristics of IoT applications that can be modeled using the framework, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the amount of memory and storage required to run an application under the framework, which is related to data structures (cs.DS).
